---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import headshot from "../assets/cody-anthony.jpg";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Cody Anthony is a documentation strategist who shapes how complex software products are documented and understood."
>
  <section class="about-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-intro__grid">
        <div class="hero-text-col">
          <p class="section__eyebrow">About Me</p>
          <h1>Engineering documentation that scales with the software it describes.</h1>

          <p>
            I'm a documentation strategist shaping how complex software
            products are documented and understood. In enterprise environments,
            I've owned the structure and delivery of developer guides, API
            references, and solution frameworks. My focus is writing the
            documentation and engineering the systems that scale it:
            information architecture, content modeling, and process automation.
          </p>

          <p>
            I design documentation systems for the teams who contribute to
            them. Instructional design and UX principles inform the content
            structure, self-service governance, and the contribution guidelines
            that hold a documentation system together as it grows.
          </p>

          <div class="identity__cta">
            <Button
              href="/cody-anthony-resume.pdf"
              variant="primary"
              icon="↓"
              download={true}
              external={false}
            >
              Download Resume (PDF)
            </Button>
            <Button
              href="https://linkedin.com/in/codyanthony"
              variant="default"
              external={true}
            >
              Connect on LinkedIn
            </Button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image-col">
          <div class="portrait portrait--sm">
            <Image
              src={headshot}
              alt="Cody Anthony"
              width={260}
              height={260}
              densities={[2]}
              class="portrait__img"
              loading="eager"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose-wide">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What colleagues say</p>
      <h2>Working with me, in their words.</h2>

      <blockquote>
        <p>
          He consistently demonstrated exceptional technical depth, strong
          ownership, and a deep commitment to customer experience. He led
          complex documentation workloads end-to-end, spanning user guides, API
          content, infrastructure-as-code material, and in-product help, and his
          work directly influenced engineering and design decisions. Senior
          technical leaders regularly praised the clarity, accuracy, and
          precision he brought to deeply technical domains.
        </p>
        <cite>— Samantha Lindsey, documentation manager, AWS (managed Cody directly)</cite>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote>
        <p>
          I was fortunate to work with him on a complicated content migration
          project. Cody developed the initial set of tooling and scripts that
          were essential to making the migration relatively quick. These scripts
          were carefully developed, well documented, and successfully used for
          many sets of content conversion. Other writers have been able to build
          on this quality engineering work to improve the migration process.
        </p>
        <cite
          >— Duncan Mackenzie, engineering and documentation leader, AWS (former
          Head of Docs, Stripe)</cite
        >
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Cody is a fantastic technical writer and content designer. He
          implemented mechanisms that enabled strong collaboration inside Amazon
          and with technical writers at an external service provider we
          partnered with. He designed the structure of our user guide,
          prioritized the most critical content, and always delivered
          bar-raising content on schedule or ahead of schedule, well calibrated
          for customers with varying levels of background knowledge.
        </p>
        <cite>— Eric Chapman, Product Manager, AWS (worked with Cody on the same team)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose-wide">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">// Skills, Tools &amp; Technologies</p>
      <h2>What I work with.</h2>

      <div class="skill-groups">
        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-group__title">Documentation and content design</h3>
          <ul class="skill-chips">
            <li class="skill-chip">API documentation</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Developer guides</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Content strategy</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Content design</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">UX writing</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Information architecture</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Content modeling</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Style guides</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Microcopy</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Release notes</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Tutorials</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">CLI and SDK references</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-group__title">Tools and platforms</h3>
          <ul class="skill-chips">
            <li class="skill-chip">Git</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">GitHub</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">GitLab</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Markdown</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">AsciiDoc</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">DocBook</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">XML</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">OpenAPI</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Confluence</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Jira</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Figma</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Cloudscape Design System</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Oxygen XML Editor</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">VS Code</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Cursor</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-group__title">AI and automation</h3>
          <ul class="skill-chips">
            <li class="skill-chip">Claude</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">ChatGPT</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Gemini</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Cline</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Q Developer CLI</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Model Context Protocol (MCP)</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Prompt engineering</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Agentic workflows</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">GenAI tool development</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Content automation</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Process automation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="skill-group">
          <h3 class="skill-group__title">Development</h3>
          <ul class="skill-chips">
            <li class="skill-chip">Python</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">JavaScript</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Node.js</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">HTML/CSS</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">REST APIs</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">JSON/YAML</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">CI/CD pipelines</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Docs-as-code</li>
            <li class="skill-chip">Static site generators</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <div class="identity__cta">
        <Button href="/case-studies/" variant="primary">
          View Case Studies →
        </Button>
        <Button
          href="https://linkedin.com/in/codyanthony"
          variant="default"
          external={true}
        >
          Connect on LinkedIn
        </Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
